annotation.TEXT: BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Metal Version (reused)
Also, I can now access every palm tree level as well!
Okay, that wasn't too tough after taking a moment to plan out my moves. Just gotta be fast when dealing with the second turn block bridge.

Oh, man. This one will likely end Reimu's death-less streak. (How many times have I said that now?) The upper part isn't too tough, but the lower part requires absolute precision when making the bounce up to the goal moon!
Once you've killed the upper-left enemy, then go and take out the remaining Sakuya if you haven't already. Should be fairly easy.
And, once again, the turn didn't auto-switch, so I'll reenter and Start+Select to force the switch.
Whoa, that was a big time bonus. Wait, did that level actually give me 300 seconds instead of the usual 60?
BGM: Ninja Gaiden 2 NES - Act 3-2 (reused)
Level 63...
Hey there, HAM radio operators, and welcome back to Hakurei Adventure Mission! It's time to take on the 60s and land a man on the MOON!!! So, let's start with level 60...

Cool. Now, even though it may look like you can simply walk from platform to platform up top, I wouldn't try that, due to how glitchy custom blocks' corners can be. Also, these blocks down here can't Kaizo trap me, right?
BGM: Super Mario World - Here We Go!
Whoa! Think fast! Fortunately, I was given enough time to react here. Now, just keep jumping from platform to platform with the rhythm of the ON/OFF switching.
BGM: Star Fox 2 - Fortuna Underground Base
I wonder what that level name translates to? (According to SuperSupermario24, it translates to "Last Mission", which is fitting. Thanks!)
Also, we're halfway through the 60s. Next is level 65...
So, which of those options will it be? Well, I'm going to let you guys vote on this one!
BGM: Mega Man X - Boomer Kuwanger's Stage (reused)
Now for level 61, which is way over here...
Level 66...

Note: If you destroy the lower hat first, the level becomes practically unwinnable, due to the upper hat being out of reach. (I say "practically", because I think doing a wall jump to reach it is technically possible, but I wouldn't try that outside of a TAS.)
Oh, geez! I made it, but it sure looked like Reimu's head grazed the spikes above me! (Of course Reimu would be an expert on grazing stuff and surviving!)
Now, I think if you position yourself properly, you could actually stomp bullets and farm lives here, but I'm not going to bother trying that now, as I don't want to risk a dumb death, obviously!
Gee, I wonder how overused this music track is! As for this level, it's not too hard. Just pay attention for the bullets, and be careful with your jumps near the lower-right.
Also, remember that these fences act like vines, giving you more leeway than actual fences.
Whoa! And there Reimu goes, grazing her head on something without dying again!
BGM: Super Mario Land - Birabuto Kingdom (reused)

Oh, that's interesting, how the last main level has the same music as the first main level. Anyway, there are some spikes, Thwimp dolls, and random bullets to get past here. Shouldn't be too hard, unless a random bullet ambushes you.
Ooh, I'll need to do some precision swimming here, but I don't think this'll be the most difficult level in the world.
Ah, it looks like I can now access the final level!
Okay, so the goal here is to bounce on all of the Remilias. Shouldn't be nearly as tough-looking as pumpkin head bouncing, and there's eight of them, so I should be able to get at least one 1-up!
BGM: Mega Man 3 - Snake Man's Stage (reused)
Once again, no automatic turn switch, so I'm going to have Sanae reenter that level and Start+Select to pass the turn to Reimu.

So, here are my options: I could try out the final level next, or I could try the "Extra Mission: Insanity Levels" (the palm tree levels), or I could go through the Yukari gap and try the special missions in there.

Um, what? Okay, so for some reason, the turn didn't switch after completing that level, and I think that's gonna be the case for many of the levels up here. So, to be fair, I'm going to reenter the level and quickly Start+Select to force a turn change.
Awesome! That 3-life combo was exactly enough to max out Reimu's lives! I guess I should give one of them to Sanae...

Ah, the turn switches properly here. I wonder if the inability to actually move up from levels 63 through 67 caused the turn to not switch. (Note: Level 62 was apparently set to "no-auto-move", which is why the turn switched normally there.) Okay, now for the last main level!
Oh, and also, that oddity caused the save prompt to delay its appearance until somebody made a move on the map (regardless of turn switching). That's kind of weird, but whatever. Now for level 64...
Ah, this one. Okay, what you want to do is normal jump on the lower disco hat and bounce up to the upper brown block ledges.
And, once again, another quick Start+Select to force a turn switch.
Ooh, more Sakuyas. They're easy enough to take out, but don't be too hasty. You'll want to bounce off of the upper one or her knives to reach the upper-left enemy.
Watch your head while jumping down here. Also, once you're close enough, you can just jump straight to the goal sphere.
Huh. One happened to land on the starting block, so I can extend my combo! Also, make absolutely sure you'll land on the starting block after getting rid of all of the Remilias!
Whoa, I was expecting to spin jump bounce off the knives there, not ride them like a Birdo egg. Good thing that the spikes on the left didn't kill me!
Well, I'm going to reenter that level briefly since the turn didn't switch, so...
Ah, this one. I remember watching Bear struggle with this one quite a bit, though he recently succeeded at it.

Oh, what have we here? Okay, don't make any rash moves yet. Let's hang out on the center of the starting turn block bridge while assessing the situation. (Note that the start point isn't quite over the center of that turn block bridge, so at least move a little to the right as soon as the level starts.)

You want to try to get up there quickly, before the hats have a chance to sync up and make things much trickier. Once you're up there, spin jump on the upper disco hat, then take out the lower one (you might be able to get them both in the same jump).
The ground is slippery, and you've gotta do some tricky platforming here. Oh, and when you hit the arrow block, DO NOT be holding A or B, or the ceiling will kill you!
Yeah! You gotta be good at precision swimming, and not being a moron when it comes to dodging maces helps too, but this level is definitely not the most difficult level in the world!
Nope, I'm safe during my victory march here, even if a block turns solid while overlapping me.
So now, let's check the status of this winding path...

NOTE: If you do take out the upper Sakuya without reaching the upper-left enemy, it's not completely unwinnable, as it is a six-tile high jump to get up there, so you could try for a max speed jump if that happens. (Or try to wall jump up there, but I would consider that much harder to do.)
Alright, let's get Sanae over there to take on level 62.
BGM: Diddy Kong Racing - Star City (reused)
Also, refrain from doing any kind of "victory hop" as you hit the goal moon, or you'll probably Kaizo trap yourself! But, you're not that dumb, right?
Level 68...
And with that, all of the primary levels have been completed! (And, apparently, level 69 was also a "no-auto-move" level, so the turn switched properly.)
BGM: Hatsune Miku - Po Pi Po
BGM: Ninja Gaiden NES - Act 5-3 (reused)
Just three main levels left... Now, level 67...
So, Reimu performs yet another miracle!

So, vote for one of the following: A. The final level B. The four palm tree levels C. The nine Yukari gap levels ...And we'll find out where I go next time! (Note: If B or C wins, I'll be playing the individual levels of those in numerical order.)

Yeah, you are given 300 seconds in this level! So, not only did they not put in custom music here, they left the timer as one of the default values! Well, I guess that means this would be a great life-farming level if you can get your positioning just right.
To be continued...
Heh. It's kind of funny how Reimu's the one performing most of the miracles, while Sanae's the one that's looking for donations here.
